{"title":"Coalescer race fix post-mortem","gitnotes":1,"type":"html","body":"<!doctype html>\n<html lang=\"en\">\n<head>\n<meta charset=\"utf-8\">\n<style>\n  :root { --bg:#141820; --fg:#edf0f5; --muted:#8b939e; --warn:#f0883e; --ok:#3fb950; --card:#1a2030; --border:#2d3548; }\n  body { font:15px/1.55 system-ui,sans-serif; background:var(--bg); color:var(--fg); margin:0; padding:1.5rem 2rem; max-width:50rem; }\n  h1 { font-size:1.3rem; margin:0 0 .75rem; }\n  .timeline { border-left:3px solid var(--border); margin-left:.5rem; padding-left:1.25rem; }\n  .evt { margin-bottom:1rem; position:relative; }\n  .evt::before { content:''; position:absolute; left:-1.55rem; top:.45rem; width:10px; height:10px; border-radius:50%; background:var(--warn); }\n  .evt.fixed::before { background:var(--ok); }\n  a { color:#79c0ff; text-decoration:none; }\n  a:hover { text-decoration:underline; }\n  code { background:#0004; padding:.1rem .3rem; border-radius:3px; font-size:.88em; }\n</style>\n</head>\n<body>\n<h1>In-flight map leak on rejected fetch</h1>\n<div class=\"timeline\">\n  <div class=\"evt\"><strong>Symptom</strong> — After a failed <code>getOrFetch</code>, <code>pendingCount()</code> stayed at 1; retries returned the stale rejected promise.</div>\n  <div class=\"evt\"><strong>Root cause</strong> — <a href=\"gitnotes:diff/examples/demo/cache/src/coalesce.ts#R9-R11\">early return</a> reused the map slot but synchronous throws bypassed <code>finally</code> cleanup in the old shape.</div>\n  <div class=\"evt fixed\"><strong>Fix</strong> — <a href=\"gitnotes:diff/examples/demo/cache/src/coalesce.ts#R13-R22\">Identity-checked delete</a> in <code>finally</code>; wrap fetcher with <code>Promise.resolve</code> so sync throws propagate without leaving orphans.</div>\n  <div class=\"evt fixed\"><strong>Proof</strong> — <a href=\"gitnotes:diff/examples/demo/cache/tests/coalesce.test.ts#R5-R22\">Regression tests</a> assert map is empty after reject and retry succeeds.</div>\n</div>\n</body>\n</html>"}
